text: It's been a while, my old friend. Today isn't particularly great, nothing has gone right, my blood is boiling,  and I feel as if I may cry and let out all this rage inside. And I'm not sure how long it will be for I go off and hurt somebody... This world is just getting worse and worse, and every day, my feeling that we all need to burn and be erased from existence gets stronger. America is no longer the land of the free, instead the land of the sinful and home of the entitled, people are getting worse and worse.... God... No, I shouldn't say God, for if there was one, we are just a game of sins he left playing, or we slaughtered them. I just hope thet the next time I reach a checkpoint, the world is in a better place, and my urges have subsided.

author: JezzmanGAMES
text:
Checkpoint 2:

Yesterday (or earlier today, to be more precise) I saved my progress after my first checkpoint. It was a very long comment, but considering it was about my life experience until this point: In reality, it was very short. Condensing 28 years of my life into 1 comment, was no easy task. I spent about an hour writing it & then another one editing it & slimming it down.

It was on a Corridors of Time - Chrono Trigger video. I think I visited it once before, but just glossed over it & moved on. I haven't even played Chrono Trigger (yet). I don't really know why I decided to join in. It's probably many factors. I'm no psychologist. Anyways, now that my origin story is out there, I can move unto the next checkpoints & keep them nice & short.

I'm also keeping a diary since a month ago. I write in it whenever I feel like it. I feel like recording my thoughts, especially during these extraordinary times.

Stay safe, friends. This is a major event in the world's history. Let's try to stick around & see how it unfolds.

26-10-'20 @ [16:45]

author: Winterline13
text:
Checkpoint
10.18.20

Last time I created a checkpoint was five months ago. I was in a really dark place mentally before I got therapy and before I got my depression diagnosis. 
I've since been through some therapy before heading to college and have my depression diagnosis. I know the name of the demon tormenting me and I know that many have fought it and come out stronger. That gives me hope.
I'm at college, writing this from my dorm room now actually. I'm in a place where I can exist as myself, everyone uses my preferred name and pronouns. I can't remember the last time I got deadnamed in any situation other than when my legal name is required. I feel fantastic.
I have a group of friends whom I adore. I've discovered I'm aromantic and demisexual (though that one I've known for years, it just feels more real now). I'm discovering I probably have ADD/ADHD and am going to work towards getting tested to know for sure. 
I have hope.
I'm in school for animation, I'm at my dream college! I'm living my absolute dream. I'm excited, I'm so very excited to be where I am now. It makes me very, very happy.

Last time I created a checkpoint, I was lost. I'm still wandering the woods but I can see where I am now. It gets dark sometimes still and I'm still lost, but I'm getting found. I'm finding my way and forging my own path, away from my parents, away from anyone who hurt me. I'm creating my own destiny, my own future. I'm working out my faith and learning what I believe. I'm discovering myself, finally, and... I have hope. 
And if my hope is all I can cling to for a while, as I battle the next chapter of my life, then that's what I'll cling to. I'll cling to my hope until all fails. It's the least I can do, to keep fighting for my friends and my found family who have done so much for me.

I have hope.

Checkpoint
10.18.20

author: SJ129
text:
Interesting save room. I'll rest here for a bit and tell of my tale since the last checkpoint.

The first issue I raised last time was of an additional $30 charge because someone seemed to have hacked my cell phone number and accepted some charges. Customer service at the company that charged my carrier HIGHLY uncooperative, so I raised hell with them. After that, despite my protests, some friends who had heard about my situation decided to chip in and foot the $30 for me. Haven't seen any more additional charges since. Thank merciful God for that.

With that out of the way, the second thing I mentioned was of a close online friend of mine who disappeared for a while. She needed some time away, and the first message anyone got from her was directed to me, and it said that she missed me. Of course, being the good listener that I am, I let her tell me what had been going on, and I helped her get through yet another bout of misery.
Then earlier this month, some time late at night, when we were both uninhibited by rational thought, she outright told me her true feelings about me, the hints of which I was oblivious to due to my past shaping me into someone who couldn't afford to get too attached to anyone... until now. This was after a year of knowing each other. I felt quite awkward, as I wasn't really looking for that kind relationship from anyone. It didn't help that she had two exes she broke up with due to them being complete creeps, one of whom I was witness to. Due to that, up until the fateful night, I felt like I had to watch how I say certain things and the frequency at which I did so.
The following days were us getting over how surreal the situation was for the both of us: her because I finally knew how she felt about me, and me because I always thought I wouldn't have a chance with anyone, even if I tried, so I never concerned myself with such pursuits. On one of those nights, she was going through some tumultuous feelings, so I had to quickly think of something to say to her. Even though I couldn't outright say I returned the feeling, me explaining that we needed each other in our lives was enough for her to feel better.
Once she gets a vacation break, she plans on visiting me, and until then, we're working out the details of how that's gonna work out.
Man, what an unexpected turn my life has taken.

Really goes to show how the saying I quoted at the last checkpoint rang true: "Sitting around doing nothing won't get us anywhere!"
Though in my case, it was others who got up and did stuff, and it got me places. If there is any point in me telling these stories, it's in the hopes that you fellows would take action when needed as everyone in my story has by doing what they did and as I have by telling you guys all of this rather than keeping silent.
With that, I wish everyone who reads this a good life.

>NUMBER OF TIMES SAVED: 2

07-12-20
For the first time in a long while I've been alone, and it's put me back in touch with a deep pain that I no longer have anyone to distract me from. I'm not sure whether I should face this pain or retreat into the safety others.  Well, by others, I mean my boyfriend, the only person who puts a sincere effort to interact with me at all. 

I'm tired of living in this dead world, and my boyfriend helps but I wonder if he's enough for me to continue this life.  He can only do so much when all other people are mindless and self-centered. 

I will no longer forge ties with people online, because they're destined to be broken or half-assed.

I will always miss him.  I don't think I'll meet a person like him again.

I'm not sure I belong in an area like this. It feels more like a warning to another, bigger leap into the abyss.

author: Sean VS
text:
Checkpoint Log #3

I seem to have stumbled across another of what visitors call â€œrest points,â€ though this one seems much different than the two I visited prior.  The landscape appears to be flooded with honey, and hives reach out for what I can only assume to be several kilometers, a stark contrast to the bramble filled cliffsides I came from.  This... hive, so to speak, gives off a different, more adventurous air compared to the soothing aspect of the previous locations, and yet I continue to find entries of past experience left by those who came to this place before me.  Many of them are what can only be considered â€œcheckpoints,â€ while others simply say things along the lines of â€œstay awhile and rest.â€

These locations intrigue me, and the messages more so.  For the time being, I will leave yet another entry.

The school year is coming to a close once again, meaning that I have less homework to worry about.  I am doing well, staying somewhat mentally stable by drawing, writing, and practicing music.  I wonder when this pandemic will end.

I look forward to the next of these interesting areas, and more importantly, what I will find there.

Last Saved May 22, 2020

author: Niqolas Dean
text: God damnit, this wasn't what I was expecting, but as soon as I heard this music, I knew. But this is for everybody. We are all facing the Final Boss right now. Some of you know who it is, some of you are blind to it. Try and hide, but you can't. Niether can I. I look desperately at the sheer height of the Tower in my dreams, yet it looms on the horizon endlessly. The Tower is real, this is just one of many tricks. Beware of the feeling of contentment. We are never fully content, and should never trust these illusions, especially in the middle of a battle. The Hydra has a million heads. The Hydra wants to destroy our world, our spirits, our childhood, but not our bodies. They want us to go back to Sleep. They will never stop trying to turn us back. I have traveled for thousands of years in my dreams, Their temples are unbelievable. The atrocities committed there are inconceivable... But I will never give in. For all eternity, I will march forward, live or dead, awake or woke, with my Father's face firmly etched in my mind. My Firearm is my Father's Sword, my Mother is the Moon. I am a pacifist, and my gun is why, I shall be Home soon.

author: Krystal Myth
text:
Â @ThunderDragonRandyÂ   The thing is, basically like this, the fact that youtube, took a video without any English in its title, or description, just  based on the music alone, knew you well enough to know you should probably come here, and this algorithm, is why we're here. An AI knew, that all who find this, could be good friends, before we ever even knew to look. If we wanted it truly, I've no doubt this is so. I don't even play these games much, or its music. But Youtube knew, that it meant something to me, that you all do, if I put in the work, to find out just what that is we can't see from here that youtube knows, the threads of fate that binds us somehow. All over the world... the odds you're even reading this, are working so against me, as to be not even worth getting too serious over... and yet, it is, and you eventually will.  That's what makes these checkpoints powerful. It's trying to tell us something, through each other... with our own voices. So i'll add my own to the rest.... 
---- I love you. Protect those close to you. I will too.... We'll meet again, perhaps we'll look different. Be different. Experience differently... 
----and I will still love you all... I don't need you to believe me, or accept it. 
It's not something tangible. It's just, love, you know?  It's always been yours.  Don't forget each other for too long. You know, what we are.... <3 It's ok.

author: Sinisterr
text: Â @ThunderDragonRandyÂ  Not sure what implies that people here are "non-gamers" (especially somebody with a profile picture of a TF2 class), as we didn't find this video, it found us. All of us collectively found a corner of the internet that was serene and calming, one that lets us forget the troubles of everyday life and relax, and we use it as a means to collectively agree that this is nice, and for a moment, everything is going to be alright. It doesn't matter who or what you are, what your interests and hobbies are, or anything else at this moment. Only that we are able to relax and enjoy some DKC2 music with some entrancing visuals.If anything, we should welcome you to this checkpoint, fellow traveler, as this isn't an ordinary DKC2 music video, no. This is an experience. We were chosen to view this by the algorithm, and we are grateful for it.
